Govvy - sounds like: guv-E

n. 

* A spy that works for a governing body. 
* A nickname referring to people that work for the government.

First used as a nickname in 1996 many people have asked what it ment and so the meaning was fixed back then. Since that time many people have used the word in their literacy writings. Upon a Google search you will see a fair few sites using the word.

Ref: http://www.govvy.co.uk

